{"tid":1947563,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"八名韋斯咸球員出現武漢肺炎病徵","createTime":"2020-03-28T11:15:11.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-29T02:58:09.000Z","uid":165817,"like":4,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":10,"replies":[{"pid":"8137e4371658811e329c9457af87f1263d7f22ff","tid":1947563,"uid":165817,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-28T11:15:11.000Z","msg":"West Ham have eight players in self-isolation showing mild symptoms of coronavirus.<br />\n<br />\nHammers vice-chairman Karren Brady revealed the number in her column in The Sun as the pandemic continues to cause major disruption to the sporting calendar.<br />\n<br />\nBrady wrote: &quot;I am relieved to say they are all showing mild symptoms and, along with their families, seem to be well.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;But it is no more than a handshake, sneeze or cough away from any of us, so no one should be complacent.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nEarlier this month, Brady stated this season's Premier League should be declared &quot;null and void&quot; if it can't be finished due to the coronavirus pandemic.<br />\n<br />\nBut Brady says Premier Leagues are committed to finishing the season.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;When we - all Premier League clubs - last spoke, we agreed to get going again as soon as possible,&quot; Brady said.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;And that games will run into July, if required, to get this campaign finished. This is the plan. This is what we want to deliver."},{"pid":"ab16a1cba89561bd5fa9ebe1e29b34d692f7021e","tid":1947563,"uid":19552,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-28T11:24:04.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9f704a1fa3b0ac0b2a304b185180611a2c72d4b9","tid":1947563,"uid":7435,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-28T11:26:58.000Z","msg":"屌你老母死曼狗.jpg<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/fac